.TH shell_docs 3 "stdlib 7.3" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
shell_docs \- Functions used to render EEP-48 style documentation for a shell.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This module can be used to render function and type documentation to be printed in a shell. This is the module that is used to render the documentation accessed through the shell through \fIh/1,2,3\fR. Example:

.IP
.nf
1> h(maps,new,0).

  -spec new() -> Map when Map :: #{}.

Since:
  OTP 17.0

  Returns a new empty map.

  Example:

    > maps:new().
    #{}

.fi

.PP
This module formats and renders EEP-48 documentation of the format \fIapplication/erlang+html\fR. For more information about this format see Documentation Storage in EDoc's User's Guide. It can also render any other format of "text" type, although those will be rendered as is.

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBchunk_element() ::\fR
\fB          {chunk_element_type(),\fR
\fB           chunk_element_attrs(),\fR
\fB           chunk_elements()} |\fR
\fB          binary().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBchunk_element_attr() :: {atom(), unicode:chardata()}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBchunk_element_attrs() :: [chunk_element_attr()].\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBchunk_element_block_type() ::\fR
\fB          p | 'div' | blockquote | br | pre | ul | ol | li | dl | dt |\fR
\fB          dd | h1 | h2 | h3 | h4 | h5 | h6.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBchunk_element_inline_type() :: a | code | em | strong | i | b.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBchunk_element_type() ::\fR
\fB          chunk_element_inline_type() | chunk_element_block_type().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
The HTML tags allowed in \fIapplication/erlang+html\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBchunk_elements() :: [chunk_element()].\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBconfig() ::\fR
\fB          #{encoding => unicode | latin1,\fR
\fB            columns => pos_integer(),\fR
\fB            ansi => boolean()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
The configuration of how the documentation should be rendered.

encoding
.RS 2
Configure the encoding that should be used by the renderer for graphical details such as bullet-points. By default 
\fIshell_docs\fR uses the value returned by \fIio:getopts()\fR.

.RE

ansi
.RS 2
Configure whether ansi escape codes should be used to render graphical details such as bold and underscore. By default 
\fIshell_docs\fR will try to determine if the receiving shell supports ansi escape codes. It is possible to override the automated check by setting the kernel configuration parameter \fIshell_docs_ansi\fR to a \fIboolean/0\fR value.

.RE

columns
.RS 2
Configure how wide the target documentation should be rendered. By default 
\fIshell_docs\fR used the value returned by \fIio:columns()\fR. It is possible to override this default by setting the stdlib configuration parameter \fIshell_docs_columns\fR to a \fIpos_integer/0\fR value.

.RE


.RE
.B
\fBdocs_v1() :: #docs_v1{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
The record holding EEP-48 documentation for a module. You can use \fIcode:get_doc/1\fR to fetch this information from a module.


.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBnormalize(Docs) -> NormalizedDocs\fR
\fB                   when\fR
\fB                       Docs :: chunk_elements(),\fR
\fB                       NormalizedDocs :: chunk_elements().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
This function can be used to do whitespace normalization of \fIapplication/erlang+html\fR documentation.


.RE
.B
\fBrender(Module, Docs, Config) -> unicode:chardata()\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                    Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                    Config :: config();\fR
\fB            (Module, Function, Docs) -> Res\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                    Function :: atom(),\fR
\fB                    Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                    Res ::\fR
\fB                        unicode:chardata() | {error, function_missing}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Render module or function documentation.

.PP
Renders the module documentation if called as \fIrender(Module, Docs, Config)\fR.

.PP
Equivalent to \fIrender(Module, Function, Docs, #{})\fR if called as \fIrender(Module, Function, Docs)\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBrender(Module, Function, Docs, Config) -> Res\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                    Function :: atom(),\fR
\fB                    Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                    Config :: config(),\fR
\fB                    Res ::\fR
\fB                        unicode:chardata() | {error, function_missing};\fR
\fB            (Module, Function, Arity, Docs) -> Res\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                    Function :: atom(),\fR
\fB                    Arity :: arity(),\fR
\fB                    Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                    Res ::\fR
\fB                        unicode:chardata() | {error, function_missing}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Render function documentation.

.PP
Renders the function documentation if called as \fIrender(Module, Function, Docs, Config)\fR.

.PP
Equivalent to \fIrender(Module, Function, Arity, Docs, #{})\fR if called as \fIrender(Module, Function, Arity, Docs)\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBrender(Module, Function, Arity, Docs, Config) -> Res\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                    Function :: atom(),\fR
\fB                    Arity :: arity(),\fR
\fB                    Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                    Config :: config(),\fR
\fB                    Res ::\fR
\fB                        unicode:chardata() | {error, function_missing}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Render the documentation for a function.


.RE
.B
\fBrender_callback(Module, Docs, Config) -> unicode:chardata()\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                             Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                             Config :: config();\fR
\fB                     (Module, Callback, Docs) -> Res\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                             Callback :: atom(),\fR
\fB                             Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                             Res ::\fR
\fB                                 unicode:chardata() |\fR
\fB                                 {error, callback_missing}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Render all callbacks in a module or callback documentation.

.PP
Renders a list with all callbacks if called as \fIrender_callback(Module, Docs, Config)\fR.

.PP
Equivalent to \fIrender_callback(Module, Callback, Docs, #{})\fR if called as \fIrender_callback(Module, Callback, Docs)\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBrender_callback(Module, Callback, Docs, Config) -> Res\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                             Callback :: atom(),\fR
\fB                             Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                             Config :: config(),\fR
\fB                             Res ::\fR
\fB                                 unicode:chardata() |\fR
\fB                                 {error, callback_missing};\fR
\fB                     (Module, Callback, Arity, Docs) -> Res\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                             Callback :: atom(),\fR
\fB                             Arity :: arity(),\fR
\fB                             Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                             Res ::\fR
\fB                                 unicode:chardata() |\fR
\fB                                 {error, callback_missing}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Render callback documentation.

.PP
Renders the callback documentation if called as \fIrender_callback(Module, Callback, Docs, Config)\fR.

.PP
Equivalent to \fIrender_callback(Module, Callback, Arity, Docs, #{})\fR if called as \fIrender_callback(Module, Callback, Arity, Docs)\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBrender_callback(Module, Callback, Arity, Docs, Config) -> Res\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             Module :: module(),\fR
\fB                             Callback :: atom(),\fR
\fB                             Arity :: arity(),\fR
\fB                             Docs :: docs_v1(),\fR
\fB                             Config :: config(),\fR
\fB                             Res ::\fR
\fB                                 unicode:chardata() |\fR
\fB                                 {error, callback_missing}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Render the documentation of a callback in a module.


.RE
.B
\fBrender_type(Module, Docs, Config) -> unicode:chardata()\fR
